Luke Will is Leads a group of men against the blacks at the Marshall Plantation. Luke Will has rough manners and a rough temperament. Luke Will possesses outdated ideas, crass manners, and dirty hands. In addition to being a ruffian, Will is in many ways a coward. Before going to the lynching, for example, Luke and his men get drunk so that they can have the willpower to undertake the violence ahead of them. Their need to exist as a drunk mob shows them as insecure men who pray on others in order to achieve a sense of superiority. Luke Will, however, is just a troublemaker not worthy of admiration.